    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Benefit:</strong> The acid or fire effects of the affected talent adhere to the affected creature(s), causing more damage the next round. When a creature takes acid or fire damage from the affected talent, that creature takes damage equal to the talent&#8217;s caster level at the start of its next turn. The damage is acid or fire, as determined by the spell&#8217;s descriptor. If a burning talent has both the fire and acid descriptor, the caster chooses what kind of damage is dealt by the burning talent effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> +2 spell points</p>\n",
